
- install djano-next from https://github.com/Tiendil/django-next
  Do not foget add import path, for example, like in that command:

  export PYTHONPATH=$PYTHONPATH:"<path to django-next>"

- configure postgre

- configure celery and rabbitmq

see: http://wiki.postgresql.org/wiki/Detailed_installation_guides

- near settings.py create settings_local.py, where you can redefine
  all needed variables (for example see settings_local_example.py)

  specify databese credentials

- ./manage.py syncdb
- ./manage.py migrate

  if migrate raise error, try migrate by application, like './manage.py migrate turns'
  
  migrations will be recreated after code will be stabilized

- prepair database:

  - from admin create first turn
  - from admin create some places
  - from admin create some roads, to get fullconnected graph
  - ./manage.py roads_update_roads
  - ./manage.py roads_update_waymarks

- THE END